      "content": "that makes sense, i'll look into the docs. but i'm curious about something though. when people bring up these concerns, it sometimes feels like the school and the media treat them as if they're just being \"bigoted\" or \"uninformed,\" rather than just having genuine disagreements on how kids should be raised. is it fair to say that the mainstream view is that these curriculum changes are just a standard part of modern education, while the opposition is seen as being on the wrong side of progress?",
